1
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:27,243
This is Clete Roberts
reporting from Phenix City, Alabama.

2
00:00:27,411 --> 00:00:30,938
I'm here to learn the truth
about Phenix City.

3
00:00:31,115 --> 00:00:33,879
Like many other Americans
and people throughout the world...

4
00:00:34,051 --> 00:00:36,485
...I had heard the story
of the criminal syndicate...

5
00:00:36,653 --> 00:00:39,918
...which allegedly controlled this city
for many years.

6
00:00:40,090 --> 00:00:42,524
And I'd heard the tale
of the cold-blooded murder...

7
00:00:42,693 --> 00:00:44,285
...of Albert A. Patterson...

8
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:46,656
...Alabama's attorney general nominate.

9
00:00:46,830 --> 00:00:49,094
The declaration of martial law
in Phenix City...

10
00:00:49,266 --> 00:00:51,063
...was also well-known to me.

11
00:00:51,235 --> 00:00:55,672
And like many of you, I had read of it
in the pages of national news magazines...

12
00:00:55,839 --> 00:01:00,799
<i>...such as LIFE, TIME, Look,
and The Saturday Evening Post.</i>

13
00:01:01,778 --> 00:01:05,475
Recently, I learned that
the Columbus, Georgia Ledger Enquirer...

14
00:01:05,649 --> 00:01:07,879
...was being considered
for a Pulitzer prize.

15
00:01:08,051 --> 00:01:10,918
A prize later won for the part it played...

16
00:01:11,088 --> 00:01:14,888
...in unmasking the criminal syndicate
here in Phenix City.

17
00:01:15,058 --> 00:01:17,390
This prompted me as a reporter
to come down here...

18
00:01:17,561 --> 00:01:19,461
...to find out what really happened.

19
00:01:19,630 --> 00:01:23,122
To learn how the good people
of Phenix City had triumphed over evil...

20
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,962
...and how democracy
had successfully asserted itself...

21
00:01:26,136 --> 00:01:29,128
...over a very real dictatorship.

22
00:01:29,306 --> 00:01:31,137
I learned many shocking facts...

23
00:01:31,308 --> 00:01:34,004
...from the people who lived
the Phenix City story...

24
00:01:34,178 --> 00:01:35,975
...the real people involved.

25
00:01:36,146 --> 00:01:38,580
You will meet them in a moment
as I talk with them...

26
00:01:38,749 --> 00:01:41,149
...and I warn you
that what you hear them say...

27
00:01:41,318 --> 00:01:43,377
...you will find hard to believe...

28
00:01:43,554 --> 00:01:45,181
...but they speak the truth.

29
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:47,653
I warn you too
that what you are about to see...

30
00:01:47,824 --> 00:01:50,349
...in the picture
which follows my news report...

31
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:51,858
...will shock you too.

32
00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:54,020
It is brutal, it's shocking...

33
00:01:54,198 --> 00:02:00,364
...but it is based upon the actual story
of what happened here in Phenix City.

34
00:02:01,505 --> 00:02:05,305
We in the news reporting profession
are agreed that this gentleman...

35
00:02:05,475 --> 00:02:07,204
- How are you, Ed.
- Fine. How are you?

36
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:08,435
Fine. Come on down, Ed.

37
00:02:08,612 --> 00:02:12,104
This gentleman
is one of the great reporters in the South.

38
00:02:12,282 --> 00:02:14,182
He's Ed Strickland
of The Birmingham News.

39
00:02:14,351 --> 00:02:17,718
Ed, will you look right straight
at the United States of America now...

40
00:02:17,888 --> 00:02:23,485
...while I ask you some questions about
the job of reporting that you have done...

41
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:25,457
...on the Phenix City story?

42
00:02:25,629 --> 00:02:29,497
When did you first become interested in
the situation in Phenix City? How long ago?

43
00:02:29,666 --> 00:02:32,692
About 1950, Clete,
I first went to Phenix City...

44
00:02:32,869 --> 00:02:37,203
...and began making some investigation
for my paper from time to time...

45
00:02:37,374 --> 00:02:39,569
...and later for another organization.

46
00:02:39,743 --> 00:02:41,904
I want you
to tell those people right there.

47
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:43,740
Look at them while you talk to me...

48
00:02:43,914 --> 00:02:47,145
...because I want them to have a good look
at a great reporter.

49
00:02:47,317 --> 00:02:51,811
How many months did you spend
or years did you spend on the story?

50
00:02:51,989 --> 00:02:53,957
On the story of the Patterson murder...

51
00:02:54,124 --> 00:02:56,922
...of course it began on June 18th
of 1954.

52
00:02:57,094 --> 00:02:59,790
I went there within three hours
after the murder...

53
00:02:59,963 --> 00:03:04,229
...and stayed for six months
without a break...

54
00:03:04,401 --> 00:03:07,336
...with more than two or three days
at a time during that time.

55
00:03:07,504 --> 00:03:11,201
You mind telling us about the news break
from the point of view of a reporter...

56
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:14,902
...that you got
on the news of Mr. Patterson's murder?

57
00:03:15,078 --> 00:03:17,069
I did have a wonderful news break
in that...

58
00:03:17,247 --> 00:03:19,977
...I happened to be
trying to reach Mr. Patterson...

59
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:23,017
...via long-distance telephone
at the time of the shooting.

60
00:03:23,186 --> 00:03:28,055
And got the word immediately
from the operator in Columbus, Georgia...

61
00:03:28,225 --> 00:03:30,216
...that Mr. Patterson had been killed.

62
00:03:30,394 --> 00:03:33,659
A few moments later, with my
photographer, I was on the way down there.

63
00:03:33,830 --> 00:03:38,995
Ed, do you think that the story about
conditions that existed in Phenix City...

64
00:03:39,169 --> 00:03:41,228
...has been exaggerated in any way?

65
00:03:41,405 --> 00:03:44,033
It has not been exaggerated.
It could not be exaggerated.

66
00:03:44,207 --> 00:03:48,735
From my knowledge of the things
that went on there prior to the shooting...

67
00:03:48,912 --> 00:03:51,210
...and sometime thereafter...

68
00:03:51,381 --> 00:03:54,373
...it would be impossible to exaggerate,
I would believe.

69
00:03:54,551 --> 00:03:56,781
You put this all down in a book,
have you not?

70
00:03:56,953 --> 00:03:57,977
Yes, I have.

71
00:03:58,155 --> 00:04:00,817
<i>Gene Wortsman
of the Birmingham Post-Herald and myself...</i>

72
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:03,960
...have collaborated
in writing a book on Phenix City.

73
00:04:04,127 --> 00:04:05,151
Another question.

74
00:04:05,329 --> 00:04:07,320
Do you believe
that the so-called machine...

75
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:10,295
...the threat, still exists in Phenix City?

76
00:04:10,467 --> 00:04:11,866
I'm sorry to say that it does.

77
00:04:12,035 --> 00:04:15,869
It will be some time, apparently
before it will be completely eradicated.

78
00:04:16,039 --> 00:04:19,167
There is evidence
that it is trying to come back.

79
00:04:19,343 --> 00:04:20,367
Thank you very much.

80
00:04:20,544 --> 00:04:22,375
Ed Strickland of The Birmingham News...

81
00:04:22,546 --> 00:04:28,485
...who played one of the major roles
in bringing this story to public attention.

82
00:04:29,753 --> 00:04:31,948
With me now is Mr. Hugh Bentley...

83
00:04:32,122 --> 00:04:33,749
...a resident of Phenix City...

84
00:04:33,924 --> 00:04:38,657
...whose life was constantly threatened
and whose home was dynamited...

85
00:04:38,829 --> 00:04:43,061
...because of his determination
to fight the criminal syndicate.

86
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:47,932
Do you believe, Mr. Bentley,
that these people who blew up your home...

87
00:04:48,105 --> 00:04:53,133
...knew that your family was in the house
at the time the dynamite was detonated?

88
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:54,334
Oh, yes...

89
00:04:54,511 --> 00:05:00,643
...we've been dealing with a problem here
of organized crime...

90
00:05:00,817 --> 00:05:03,513
...operated by the syndicate.

91
00:05:03,687 --> 00:05:08,056
It was one of the acts of violence,
of about 14 or 15...

92
00:05:08,225 --> 00:05:10,386
...that was perpetrated on our people.

93
00:05:11,361 --> 00:05:14,853
Mr. Bentley,
after these constant acts of terrorism...

94
00:05:15,031 --> 00:05:17,591
...these threats against yours
and your family's life...

95
00:05:17,768 --> 00:05:21,898
...why did you, and why do you continue
to live in Phenix City?

96
00:05:22,072 --> 00:05:26,441
Well, I was born and raised here,
and this is my home.

97
00:05:26,610 --> 00:05:30,979
And during this...
During the past 25 years...

98
00:05:31,148 --> 00:05:35,312
...l've had an opportunity
to teach a lot of children...

99
00:05:35,485 --> 00:05:37,476
...in my Sunday school class.

100
00:05:37,654 --> 00:05:40,350
During that time, actually,
we won a lot of them to Christ.

101
00:05:40,524 --> 00:05:46,622
And we feel like that there's more good
in the community than there is evil.

102
00:05:46,797 --> 00:05:51,166
We're basing all our strength of faith
in the good of our community...

103
00:05:51,334 --> 00:05:54,735
...hoping someday
that they will rise up...

104
00:05:54,905 --> 00:06:00,707
...and throw off
this ugly reputation it has...

105
00:06:00,877 --> 00:06:03,869
Our town has had for the past 100 years.

106
00:06:04,047 --> 00:06:08,484
I feel like it's a dirty filthy code...

107
00:06:08,652 --> 00:06:10,620
...that I inherited from my father...

108
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:14,314
...that I don't wanna hand down
to my children.

109
00:06:15,225 --> 00:06:17,455
Thank you, Mr. Bentley.

110
00:06:17,928 --> 00:06:19,793
One of the men who worked...

111
00:06:19,963 --> 00:06:22,727
...one might say fought,
side by side with Mr. Bentley...

112
00:06:22,899 --> 00:06:25,424
...is a member
of the Russell Betterment Association...

113
00:06:25,602 --> 00:06:30,164
...in combating the criminal syndicate
was Mr. Hugh Britton...

114
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:32,570
...also a resident of Phenix City.

115
00:06:32,742 --> 00:06:36,838
We have an appointment now
to talk with him at his house.

116
00:06:37,013 --> 00:06:40,449
How many honest elections
have you experienced here in Phenix City...

117
00:06:40,617 --> 00:06:42,744
...in your lifetime?

118
00:06:44,054 --> 00:06:45,988
Well, I'd say...

119
00:06:46,156 --> 00:06:50,923
...the only honest election that I know
anything about here in the last 43 years...

120
00:06:51,094 --> 00:06:52,789
...was one that we have held here...

121
00:06:52,963 --> 00:06:55,659
...it was a local election,
since we had our new sheriff...

122
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:58,801
...and police department here.

123
00:07:01,104 --> 00:07:05,973
I talked with Mr. Britton
before the camera was shooting.

124
00:07:06,142 --> 00:07:10,010
He told me a story about a man
who asked him once the same question.

125
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:12,148
What was that answer you gave him?

126
00:07:12,315 --> 00:07:16,251
Well, I'd have to explain
that when I was a boy...

127
00:07:16,419 --> 00:07:18,819
...that we, just for a pastime...

128
00:07:18,989 --> 00:07:21,685
...at night, used to take flashlights
and broomsticks...

129
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:24,224
...and go down to the city dump
to hunt rats.

130
00:07:24,394 --> 00:07:26,123
We killed some big ones.

131
00:07:26,296 --> 00:07:28,423
And that...

132
00:07:32,469 --> 00:07:36,405
That a rat, if you turn a light...

133
00:07:36,673 --> 00:07:39,506
...a bright light in a rat's face...

134
00:07:39,676 --> 00:07:41,166
...that he'll run for cover.

135
00:07:41,344 --> 00:07:44,711
And it didn't make any difference
whether that rat is in the city dump...

136
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:46,576
...or in the city hall.

137
00:07:47,851 --> 00:07:49,842
All right,
thank you very much, Mr. Britton.

138
00:07:51,655 --> 00:07:55,421
This gentleman you see is Quinnie Kelly,
who was pointed out to me.

139
00:07:55,592 --> 00:07:59,289
Mr. Kelly, will you come up here please?
He was pointed out to me earlier today.

140
00:07:59,462 --> 00:08:01,123
- I'm Clete Roberts.
- Kelly's my name.

141
00:08:01,298 --> 00:08:03,596
Happy to know you.
Look this way, will you please?

142
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:06,668
Would you mind taking your hat off
so the folks can see you?

143
00:08:06,836 --> 00:08:10,704
Quinnie Kelly is a janitor here in the
Russell County court house, are you not?

144
00:08:10,874 --> 00:08:12,068
Yeah, that's correct.

145
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:16,372
You are a witness, I know,
in the current murder trials...

146
00:08:16,546 --> 00:08:19,310
...now under way
in Birmingham, Alabama.

147
00:08:19,482 --> 00:08:22,645
And I have heard
that you have been threatened, is that true?

148
00:08:22,819 --> 00:08:24,810
Yeah,
I've been threatened many, many times.

149
00:08:24,988 --> 00:08:26,478
- Many, many times?
- That's right.

150
00:08:26,656 --> 00:08:28,521
How did these threats come to you?

151
00:08:28,692 --> 00:08:31,320
- Over the telephone.
- What did they say?

152
00:08:31,494 --> 00:08:32,791
Well, the first one comes...

153
00:08:32,963 --> 00:08:35,625
...he wanted me to remove my pistol
and badge, I wouldn't.

154
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:38,131
He said if I didn't remove
it I wouldn't live...

155
00:08:38,301 --> 00:08:39,768
...and if I did I wouldn't live.

156
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,335
- lf you didn't remove it?
- Yes.

157
00:08:41,504 --> 00:08:45,531
And your badge is as a deputy sheriff.
How long have you been a deputy sheriff?

158
00:08:45,709 --> 00:08:48,644
Well, I've been deputized
ever since Rhett Tanner has been here.

159
00:08:48,812 --> 00:08:52,111
I see. All right, now,
what other threats have you received?

160
00:08:52,282 --> 00:08:53,772
Well, I got a call Sunday.

161
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:57,716
Threatened and asked me had I seen what
was in the newspaper and I told him I did.

162
00:08:57,887 --> 00:09:00,287
- Uh-huh.
- And he says time is running out...

163
00:09:00,457 --> 00:09:04,188
...and if I didn't I wouldn't never live
to testify in this next trial.

164
00:09:04,361 --> 00:09:06,090
How do you feel? Does that scare you?

165
00:09:06,262 --> 00:09:08,025
We're not scared one bit in the world.

166
00:09:08,198 --> 00:09:11,031
And you're gonna go down there
and tell the truth, are you?

167
00:09:11,201 --> 00:09:14,193
I'm gonna tell the truth.
If I tell anything, it'll be the truth.

168
00:09:14,371 --> 00:09:16,202
Has anybody...? Is any guard on you?

169
00:09:16,373 --> 00:09:19,706
Anybody trying to help you stay alive
until you get to the trial?

170
00:09:19,876 --> 00:09:21,070
No, sir, they are not.

171
00:09:21,244 --> 00:09:23,769
- You carry a gun?
- Yeah, I carry a gun.

172
00:09:23,947 --> 00:09:25,710
- You know how to use it?
- Yeah.

173
00:09:25,882 --> 00:09:27,543
- Will you use it?
- Yeah, I'll use it.

174
00:09:27,717 --> 00:09:31,915
Thanks. Quinnie Kelly, ladies and gentlemen.
Janitor, right here in Russell County.

175
00:09:32,088 --> 00:09:33,817
- You're not afraid?
- No.

176
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:35,014
How about your family?

177
00:09:35,191 --> 00:09:38,092
Well, my wife's upset.
Been upset since they talked to her.

178
00:09:38,261 --> 00:09:40,320
Been in the care of a doctor
ever since she...

179
00:09:40,497 --> 00:09:44,627
- They went down there and talked to her.
- All right, thanks very much, Mr. Kelly.

180
00:09:44,801 --> 00:09:47,201
I know that you're a busy man.
Pleasure meeting you.

181
00:09:47,370 --> 00:09:48,462
- Glad to meet you.
- Goodbye, sir.

182
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:52,949
It is now my privilege
to take you with me...

183
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:55,923
...to the home
of Mrs. Albert A. Patterson.

184
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:58,063
Mrs. Patterson is the widow...

185
00:09:58,230 --> 00:10:03,668
...of the man who was murdered
on June 18th, 1954...

186
00:10:03,836 --> 00:10:08,739
...the attorney general nominate
of this state of Alabama.

187
00:10:08,908 --> 00:10:11,342
She is a grand Southern woman...

188
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:13,102
...mother of four boys...

189
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:16,146
...very proud of her son, John,
who came home from the wars...

190
00:10:16,315 --> 00:10:19,978
...and took over the task
that his father laid down...

191
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:22,382
...when he died
under an assassin's bullet.

192
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:24,648
John, today, her son...

193
00:10:24,823 --> 00:10:27,849
...is the man who must prosecute,
indict...

194
00:10:28,027 --> 00:10:32,088
...and bring to justice
the killers of his father.

195
00:10:32,464 --> 00:10:35,228
Mrs. Patterson lived here
under the threat of the machine...

196
00:10:35,401 --> 00:10:40,304
...and she can answer our question
as to what life was then like.

197
00:10:40,472 --> 00:10:42,303
We go now to her home.

198
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:44,503
How many free elections...

199
00:10:44,677 --> 00:10:47,737
...and honest elections
have you experienced here, Mrs. Patterson?

200
00:10:47,913 --> 00:10:50,507
Well, I've never experienced
any free elections here...

201
00:10:50,683 --> 00:10:54,210
...until this cleanup we had
in our city elections.

202
00:10:54,386 --> 00:10:57,014
What about John?
Do you worry about John's future at all?

203
00:10:57,189 --> 00:11:01,819
Do you think that he may be threatened
by the machine the way Mr. Patterson was?

204
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:07,995
Well,
I don't think he will be hurt in any way.

205
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:10,692
I believe he's all right.

206
00:11:10,869 --> 00:11:13,360
Do you think
that there's no offer, no chance...

207
00:11:13,539 --> 00:11:16,303
...of him being treated
the way your husband was?

208
00:11:16,475 --> 00:11:18,943
Well, I hope there's no chance.

209
00:11:20,079 --> 00:11:22,741
Mrs. Patterson,
you're obviously a woman of great courage.

210
00:11:22,915 --> 00:11:24,849
You've had the strength to carry on.

211
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:26,917
Where did that courage come from?

212
00:11:27,086 --> 00:11:29,247
Why, Mr. Roberts...

213
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:34,591
I suppose I got the courage
from being in this fight so long.

214
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:38,890
And we had friends
that were really doing their best...

215
00:11:39,064 --> 00:11:44,127
...to try to help make our town
a clean place to live in our state.

216
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:47,795
And I have sons and, of course,
I wanted them to have a chance.

217
00:11:47,973 --> 00:11:52,205
And we have good people in this town.

218
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:56,678
And they were under bondage
and they had to have freedom.

219
00:11:56,849 --> 00:11:58,009
And it just took...

220
00:11:58,183 --> 00:12:00,879
It took something terrible...

221
00:12:01,053 --> 00:12:03,647
...to get people to wake up.

222
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:10,260
And, I think, if the good people of America
could take a lesson from this...

223
00:12:10,429 --> 00:12:12,954
...to always be on the alert...

224
00:12:13,132 --> 00:12:16,624
...and go to the polls and vote.

225
00:12:16,802 --> 00:12:20,533
And do everything they can
to make a good America.

226
00:12:21,707 --> 00:12:25,939
For the past few minutes
we have been dealing in fact...

227
00:12:26,111 --> 00:12:28,944
...fact about the Phenix City story.

228
00:12:29,114 --> 00:12:32,277
The people with whom we have talked
are real people.

229
00:12:32,451 --> 00:12:33,816
The people involved...

230
00:12:33,986 --> 00:12:38,548
...in what has been described
as an infamous and sordid chapter...

231
00:12:38,724 --> 00:12:42,717
...in American city politics.

232
00:12:42,895 --> 00:12:46,387
There has been no careful rehearsal
of speech.

233
00:12:46,565 --> 00:12:48,362
